uickly on computer systems. They can be differentiated and integrated easily and can be pieced together to form spline curves. After Weierstrass approximation Theorem, polynomial sequences have acquired considerable importance not only in the variousbranches of Mathematics, but also in Physics, Chemistry and Engineering disciplines. There is a wide literature on specific polynomial sequences. But there is no literature that attempts a systematic exposition of the main basic methods for the study of a generic polynomial sequence and, at the same time, gives an overview of the main polynomial classes and related applications, at least in numerical analysis. In this book, through an elementary matrix calculus-based approach, an attempt is made to fill this gap by exposing dated and very recent results, both theoretical and applied.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aInfinitesimalrechnung. 4aNumerische Analysis. 4aPolynomsequenzen. 4aReelle Funktionen.  aPolynomial sequences, Numerical Analysis, Infinitesimal calculus, Real-valued function.1 aGualtieri, Maria Italia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNapoli, Anna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2023 Englishz978311131920908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2023z9783111318608oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831107573230 cprintz978311075723140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075724840